      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">52.228-13</ph> Alternative Payment
Protections.</title>
      <conbody outputclass="clause" class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d3469e8">As prescribed
in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="28.102-3.dita#FAR_28_102_3"
                     base="i1088607"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">28.102-3</xref>(b)</ph>, insert
the following clause:</p>
         <p outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps" class="- topic/p ">Alternative Payment Protections (July
2000)</p>
         <ol id="d3430e25" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3469e19">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> The
Contractor shall submit one of the following payment protections:</p>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3469e23">
                  <cite outputclass="MultiLine"
                        xtrc="52.228-13_d3454e36"
                        class="- topic/cite "
                        xtrf="GFI">________________________________________________________________________________</cite>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3469e27">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> The amount
of the payment protection shall be 100 percent of the contract price.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3469e32">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> The submission
of the payment protection is required within <cite outputclass="SingleLine"
                        xtrc="52.228-13_d3454e57"
                        class="- topic/cite "
                        xtrf="GFI">_________</cite> days
of contract award.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3469e40">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph> The payment
protection shall provide protection for the full contract performance
period plus a one-year period.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3469e45">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph> Except
for escrow agreements and payment bonds, which provide their own
protection procedures, the Contracting Officer is authorized to
access funds under the payment protection when it has been alleged
in writing by a supplier of labor or material that a nonpayment
has occurred, and to withhold such funds pending resolution by administrative
or judicial proceedings or mutual agreement of the parties.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d3469e50">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(f)</ph> When a
tripartite escrow agreement is used, the Contractor shall utilize
only suppliers of labor and material that signed the escrow agreement.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <p outputclass="Endofclause" class="- topic/p ">(End of clause)</p>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
